<body>

  <h1>chatXi</h1>

  <h2>What is chatXi?</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>chatXi</strong> is an experimental project focused on simulating social media
    interactions in a controlled environment. The goal is to combine traditional chat
    application features with advanced virtual social behavior powered by AI.
  </p>

  <p>
    Unlike conventional chat applications, chatXi is designed to explore how artificial
    agents can mimic real human behavior — including delayed responses, personality traits,
    emotional inconsistency, and unpredictable social actions.
  </p>

  <h2>Core Features</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Standard Chat System</strong> — Messaging features commonly found in modern
      chat applications.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Virtual Social Simulation</strong> — AI-driven users that behave like real
      humans rather than instant-response bots.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    AI participants in chatXi may respond late, initiate conversations independently,
    form opinions, provide misleading information, unfriend users, or disengage entirely —
    simulating real social dynamics.
  </p>

  <h2>Project Phases</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Phase 1:</strong> Command-line (CLI) based chat application without AI.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Phase 2:</strong> Introduction of a graphical user interface (GUI) alongside
      the CLI system.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Phase 3:</strong> Integration of limited AI bots that simulate human-like
      behavior, including delayed responses and distinct personalities.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Phase 4:</strong> Expansion of AI autonomy — bots can send, receive, accept,
      or decline friend requests and manage relationships independently.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Phase 5:</strong> Human-based AI cloning system, allowing users to create
      consent-based AI representations of themselves. These clones can interact with others
      while providing summarized interaction reports to the original user.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Objective</h2>

  <p>
    The primary objective of chatXi is to study social behavior, communication patterns,
    and ethical implications of AI-driven human simulation in digital environments.
  </p>

</body>
